90799,-0.05809860,0.07595439,-0.02196467,-0.03273195,0.05622057,-0.05813516,-0.02545939,-0.03516623,0.07772791,-0.06135382,0.02806972,0.00255028,-0.00593181,0.01537198,-0.00727600,-0.00496980,-0.04687768,0.03259481,-0.05275473,0.04485379,0.01858080,-0.03403530,-0.04303730,0.04803682,-0.03969063,-0.00176899,0.00642103,-0.08828864,0.00080313,-0.00339568,0.03077064,0.01785197,0.00575245,-0.03111094,-0.07741265,0.02866489,0.06311655,0.03396087,0.06327877,0.00449345,-0.05909474]',E'Version Constraints\n\nFastify will require a request `Accept-Version` header to be set if the route\nhas a version set, and will prefer a versioned route to a non-versioned route\nfor the same path. Advanced version ranges and pre-releases currently are not\nsupported.\n\n> ℹ️ Note:\n> Using this feature can degrade the router''s performance.\n\n```js\nfastify.route({\n  method: ''GET'',\n  url: ''/'',\n  constraints: { version: ''1.2.0'' },\n  handler: function (request, reply) {\n    reply.send({ hello: ''world'' })\n  }\n})','{"source": "fastify", "version": "5", "language": "javascript", "title": "Routes", "section_title": "Routes", "url": "https://github.com/fastify/fastify/blob/main/docs/Reference/Routes.md", "topics": "fastify,node,http,Routes", "categories": "web,javascript,rest"}');
